These title sequences incorporate visual elements reflecting each film's theme and, often silhouettes of nude or provocatively clad women set against swirling images. Maurice Binder is the Title Designer for thirteen Bond films.96 A contemporary artist usually sings during this sequence (starting with
Goldfinger
), and an instrumental version of the main track may also be featured as a leitmotif during the film, which repeats in various moods (tense, romantic, adventurous, etc.).97
